The paper deals with the design of a hybrid analog and digital transceiver structure for amplify-and-forward relay systems in massive MIMO networks. This involves signal processing, channel estimation, and spatial correlation analysis, which are all relevant to the fields of information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), control and systems engineering (cs.SY), multimedia (cs.MM), and computer communications (cs.COM).
